    "lyric_eng": "\nCome on, lulay, go to sleep\nWhen you grow up so big\nLike a maple so high\nAs hard as oak\n\nYou’ll be mama’s little helper\nBringing water for the stove\nYour papa's out doing the summer scything\nAnd mama's tending the garden\n"
