    "lyric_eng": "\nDraw in sleep, little mouse,\nso kitty doesn’t see you.\nThe mouse drove a creak cart,\nhauling in a load of sleep.\n\nNo one’s had it as good,\nas my little baby.\nGolden cords, a copper spring-pole,\na silver cradle.\n\nWho placed a cradle,\nfor the wolf and the bear?\nThey grew up,\nuncradled, unrocked.\n"
